'''WinRAR''' (a.k.a. RAR) is a [[shareware]] [[file archiver]] and [[data compression]] utility developed by Eugene Roshal. It is arguably one of the three main file archive programs for [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]], along with [[WinZip]] and [[7-Zip]]. It is one of the few applications that is able to create [[RAR (file format)|RAR]] archives natively, as the encoding method is held to be [[proprietary]].
